<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Educational TV Begins Transmission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702124194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1002 
GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Reporter Guo Lihua (6753 4409 5478)] </F>
  [Text] Shanghai, 27 Feb (XINHUA) -- Shanghai's Educational 
Television Station, the fourth television station in Shanghai, 
began transmission today. The three other television stations 
in Shanghai are: the Shanghai Television Station, the Oriental 
Television Station, and the Shanghai Cable Television Station. 
  This specialized television station is sponsored by the 
Shanghai Municipal People's Government Education and Public 
Health Office. Its programming will focus on education. It will 
serve the reform, opening up, and social development of Shanghai 
with interesting, rich, and colorful educational, scientific, 
and artistic programs. For the time being, the Shanghai 
Educational Station will air a total 15 hours of programs a day. 
Among the programs are: academic education, nonacademic 
education, old-age education, forum on educational reform, 
teachers training, educational information, culture, science, 
technology, public health, sports, law and morality, children's 
world, and colorful forum. 

</TEXT>

