<H3> <TI>   Shanghai-Pusan Container Ship Route Opens </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602171694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1511 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 26 (XINHUA) -- A container ship 
left Shanghai port in east China this afternoon for Pusan port 
in the Republic of Korea (ROK). This is the first ship route 
from Shanghai to ROK. 
  Starting today, each week a container ship will be 
dispatched 
to Pusan port. 
  The new route is managed by the Shanghai Jinjiang Shipping 
Corp. Ltd., a ten-year-old venture which also has ships going to 
Hong Kong and ports of Southeast Asia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

