<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang's Hangzhou Upgrades High-Tech Development Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602015894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0105 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602015894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, February 26 (XINHUA) -- Hangzhou, the 
capital of east China's Zhejiang Province, has over the past few 
years made great progress in upgrading its new and high 
technology development zone. 
  Official sources said that 134 million yuan in the 
construction of basic facilities, involving a floor space of 
some 200,000 sq m, was completed last year in this development 
zone. 
  With a total area of some 12 sq km, the zone, which was 
approved three years ago, is Zhejiang's only state-level 
development zone of the kind. 
  To date, local governments, colleges, scientific institutes 
and major companies all over the country as well as some Hong 
Kong and Taiwan businesses have set up more than 305 firms in 
the zone. 
  In addition, some 46 foreign-funded firms have been 
established there over the past three years, involving a total 
foreign investment of more than 80 million U.S. dollars. 
  According to sources from the management committee of the 
zone, great emphasis has been put upon the development of 
electronic information, new materials, new energy and 
biotechnologies as well as technologies to improve efficiency 
and save energy. 
  At the same time, such advanced new and high technologies as 
program-controlled switchboards, membron materials and silicon 
single crystals have been introduced and applied to production. 
  The latest statistics show that some 402 new and high 
technologies are currently being applied to production in the 
zone and will soon be spread throughout the country. 
  Over the past few years, relevant departments have made 
great 
efforts to improve the infrastructure of the zone in support of 
its development, officials from the management committee said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

