<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Steps Up Search for Economic Criminals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2702133794 Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2702133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Provincial News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] With the beginning of the New Year, Zhejiang 
provincial procuratorial organs began stepping up efforts to 
hunt down economic criminals, including those who involved in 
the crimes of accepting and taking bribes. In the period 1-15 
February, the province's procuratorial organs arrested a total 
of 12 economic criminals on the run, thus scoring an initial 
victory in hunting down fugitives. 
  The provincial procuratorate lists the number of fugitives 
who were involved in the crimes of accepting and offering bribes 
at 200. Thanks to long-term efforts, the provincial 
procuratorial organs have arrrested 100 of them. As the 
remaining 100 are still on the run, it is impossible to 
immediately conclude some of the bribery cases. On 1 January 
this year, the provincial procuratorate issued a circular in 
which concrete instructions were set forth for local 
procuratorial organs to step up efforts to hunt down fugitives. 
Upon receipt of the circular, grass-roots procuratorial organs 
began to act in line with the circular's instructions on hunting 
down criminals under their jurisdiction. 

</TEXT>

