<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Secretary Addresses Family Planning Forum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2502132494 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2502132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday morning the provincial party committee 
and government held a meeting for the leaders of city party 
committees to discuss family planning work and arrange measures 
for controlling this year's population growth. At the meeting, 
Governor Zhu Senlin signed responsibility agreements with city 
mayors on controlling 1994 population growth. 
  Xie Fei, a member of the CPC Central Committee's Political 
Bureau and secretary of the provincial party committee, 
addressed the meeting, stressing: All levels of party 
committees and governments should have a clear idea of the grim 
population situation, carry out family planning work in a 
down-to-earth manner, pay particular attention to false reports 
on family planning, do a good job in improving grass-roots 
organizations in the rural areas, ensure the implementation of 
family planning at the grass-roots level, improve the family 
planning service network, and gradually form a system which will 
lead to the systematization of family planning. 

</TEXT>

