<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shareholding System Benefits Hainan Economy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2802022094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0602 GMT 
26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2802022094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Haikou, February 26 (CNS)--Shareholding system 
enterprises have become an important force in Hainan's economy 
with 125 limited companies being approved since 1991, raising 
capital of RMB [Renminbi] 20.56 billion. 
  Some of these enterprises are set up based on state-owned 
enterprises with others created from non-state-run ones or 
formed by putting technology, capital and land into capital 
stock or by merging, joint-running or contracting. These 
shareholding enterprises are involved in tourism, industry, 
transportation and finance and have certain notable 
characteristics. 
  First, they make more reasonable the industrial structure in 
Hainan with 23 such companies engaging in tourism, 17 in 
industrial development, 16 in the development of whole pieces of 
land, seven in comprehensive agricultural development and five 
in infrastructural construction, with all achieving greater 
profits. 
  Second, these companies are an important contributor of 
funds 
for infrastructural construction in the province with some 60 
percent of fund for the construction of the Sanya International 
Airport, the Eastern Expressway and electric power stations 
coming from these companies, resulting in relieving the shortage 
of funds and speeding up infrastructural construction there. 
  Third, these companies have also become important sources of 
the local financial income with five listed companies alone 
handing in taxes of RMB 60 million last year. 
  The reason for the rapid development of these kinds of 
companies in Hainan is the market economy in the province and 
the greater autonomy of its enterprises. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

