declared the opening of the second session of the eighth 
provincial people's congress. [passage omitted] 
  [Begin recording] [Lu Chuanzan] Now, we are going to ask 
Governor Ye Liansong to deliver the work report of the Hebei 
Provincial People's Government. 
  [Ye Liansong] Fellow deputies: On behalf of the Hebei 
Provincial People's Government, I am going to deliver the 
government work report to the session for examinations and 
discussions and also ask all members of the provincial committee 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
[CPPCC] and all other personnel participating in the session as 
nonvoting delegates to give opinions on the report. [end 
recording] 
  Governor Ye Liansong's government work report consists of 
seven parts. First, review the 1993 work. Second, the guiding 
ideologies of the 1994 work and the 1994 fighting targets. 
Third, persistently combine overall progress with key 
breakthroughs and accelerate the reform work of the province as 
a whole. Fourth, strive to promote sustained, fast, and sound 
development of the national economy. Fifth, promote the 
development of science and technology, education, and culture. 
Sixth, realistically strengthen the spiritual civilization and 
the setup of democracy and the legal system. Seventh, strive to 
improve and strengthen government work. [passage omitted] 
  The participants in the second session of the seventh 
provincial CPPCC committee attended the session as nonvoting 
delegates. 

</TEXT>

