<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hebei Official Views Cotton Production Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2602013794 Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2602013794 </F>
<F P=104>  Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the emergency telephone conference held by the 
provincial government on 24 February, Vice Governor Gu Erxiong 
pointed out: Major problems existing in the province's current 
cotton production include: Peasants' enthusiasm in growing 
cotton needs to be mobilized further; some localities have not 
yet assigned cotton growing quotas to peasant households and 
plots; some localities have seen the trend of reducing the 
acreage sown to summer cotton; cotton seeds are of poor quality 
and in short supply; and peasants have not prepared sufficient 
means of production for growing cotton. 
  In light of these problems, Gu Erxiong stressed: The month 
before the spring sowing of cotton is the key to decide the 
success or failure in this year's cotton production. 
Governments at all levels should adopt feasible measures to 
successfully assign cotton growing quotas to peasants and ensure 
the scale of cotton growing acreage. 

</TEXT>

