<H3> <TI>   Political Affairs Talks Conclude in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2502162294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1551 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2502162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 25 (XINHUA) -- The political 
affairs group of the preliminary working committee for the 
preparatory committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative 
Region ended its fifth meeting here today. 
  The meeting, which started yesterday, discussed the 
relationship between the administrative and legislative organs 
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, the method of 
forming the first regional government and the method and time 
for the election of the administrative commissioner and how to 
form the administrative council and its functions and the 
establishment of a consultative committee after 1997. 
  Leader of the group said after the meeting that as the 
British side has shut the doors to talks, the preparatory 
committee will do solid work and start a new "stove" according 
to the guidelines of the Basic Law and ensure a smooth 
transition of power and the long-term stability and prosperity 
of Hong Kong. 
  The committee members urged the Chinese Government to 
publish 
as soon as possible the truth of the Sino-British talks and 
clarify the facts distorted by the white paper published by the 
British side on Feb. 24. 
  They said that it was merely an illusion for the British 
Hong 
Kong authorities to attempt to carry the framework it has 
arranged over July 1, 1997 deadline. 

</TEXT>

