<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Investment in Electronics Industry Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602171594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1528 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 26 (XINHUA) -- By the end of 1993, 
more than 5,000 Chinese electronics enterprises had overseas 
investment, with contracted foreign funds totalling 3.5 billion 
U.S. dollars, sources from the Ministry of the Electronics 
Industry said today. 
  Statistics from the customs department show that last year 
China's exports of electronics products reached 8.11 billion 
U.S. dollars, up 18.1 percent from the previous year; 
foreign-funded electronics enterprises gained an export income 
of 4.43 billion U.S. dollars, accounting for 54.6 percent of the 
total export value of electronics products. 
  In the past few years, the Chinese Government has been 
paying 
special attention to the electronics industry, and defined it as 
the state's pillar industry for key development. Early last 
year the State Council re-established the Ministry of the 
Electronics Industry to reinforce the administration and 
management of the industry. 
  Statistics show that last year the national electronics 
industry finished a total output value of 175 billion yuan, 
constituting some 5.2 percent of the country's total industrial 
output value. Of the industry's 40 kinds of major products, 32 
had big increases in output, which included ground stations for 
satellite communications, program-controlled switching, 
micro-computers, telephones and videorecorders. 
  Experts from the electronics sphere said the country's 
electronics industry is now facing new development 
opportunities, for which the reasons are: 
  The state is accelerating the construction of economic 
information systems to improve and reinforce macro-control 
means; various industries are showing great enthusiasm in using 
electronic information technology to remold traditional 
industries; the demand by national economy and social life for 
various electronic products has kept on increasing, which 
provides a broad market for the industry; many foreign companies 
have expressed interest in the Chinese market, and the industry 
has met with an unprecedented boom in foreign cooperation. 
  To speed up the readjustment of industrial and product 
structure, the ministry has defined nearly 20 key construction 
and technological remolding projects, including integrated 
circuits, mobile telecommunications, facsimile equipment, 
new-type program-controlled phone exchanges, and the 
second-phase project of video recorder and video camera. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

