<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Calls For Electrification of 200 Counties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602173794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1342 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 26 (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng 
called today for efforts to achieve electrification in 200 
counties during the 1991-95 period. 
  In a letter to a national conference on hydro-power-based 
rural electrification, which closed here today, Li asked various 
central departments and government bodies at all levels to do 
everything within their power to assist the electrification 
drive. 
  "The electrification of 200 counties will play a significant 
role in helping the rural residents in mountainous areas 
eliminate poverty, expand the local economy and promote 
ideological and cultural progress," he said. 
  According to delegates at the conference, hydro-electric 
power stations with a total generating capacity of 15 million 
kilowatts will be built in the countryside by the end of the 
century. 
  The Chinese Government plans to achieve hydro-power-based 
electrification in 200 counties by 1995 and another 300 counties 
during the 1996-2000 period. 

</TEXT>

