<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong People's Congress Second Session Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602173894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1403 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, February 26 (XINHUA) -- The second 
session of the eighth people's congress of Guangdong Province 
closed here today. 
  More than 700 deputies discussed the work report delivered 
by 
Governor Zhu Senlin and other reports. 
  According to the reports, in 1994, Guangdong's gross 
domestic 
product will increase by 15 percent, the industrial output value 
will increase by 21 percent and the gross agricultural output 
value will grow by 5 percent over 1993. 
  The investment in fixed assets will increase by 13 percent 
and the import and export value will grow by 16 percent. 
  The deputies called for enhancing agricultural development 
and increasing input into the services of science, technology, 
education and culture. 
  The session also passed two provincial regulations 
concerning 
the system of people's congress and elected five new members to 
the standing committee of Guangdong people's congress. 

</TEXT>

