<F P=103> OW0103035594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, February 28 (XINHUA) -- Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev said today Russia has consistently opposed any 
air action in Bosnia and warned that violators of a peace plan 
for the Bosnian crisis should realize the grave consequences of 
such behavior. 
  Kozyrev made the remarks at a press conference here when 
talking about the downing of four aircraft earlier today by two 
U.S. F-16 fighters in the no-fly zone over Bosnia. 
  He said that as aircraft will inevitably appear in the 
region 
sooner or later, it has become more necessary to solve all the 
issues in Bosnia through peaceful means. 
  Violators of a peace approach should realize the grave 
consequences of their behavior, he warned. 
  Kozyrev said it cannot be confirmed that the aircraft shot 
down came from the Bosnian Serb side because all the three 
warring parties possess such planes. 

