<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Official Criticizes UK Over Hong Kong Airport Debt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2802161794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1558 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2802161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, February 28 (XINHUA) -- The British Hong 
Kong authorities' fourth financing proposal on the proposed new 
airport in Hong Kong still poses a huge debt burden, a senior 
Chinese official said here Sunday [27 February]. 
  Zhu Yucheng, deputy director of XINHUA news agency Hong Kong 
branch, accused the British side of playing mathematics games, 
saying Hong Kong residents should establish a monitoring group 
to supervise the construction of the new airport. 
  Zhu said, "We have reiterated that the airport should be 
constructed in accordance with the memorandum of mutual 
understanding. But the fourth proposal put forward by the 
British side still poses a big problem: who should be 
responsible for the more than 20 billion H.K. [Hong Kong] 
dollars (2.564 billion U.S. dollars) debt." 
  He accused the Hong Kong Government of intending to shift 
the 
debt burden to the Special Administrative Region Government of 
Hong Kong by changing the provisional airport authority into the 
so-called airport corporation. 
  On the composition of the monitoring organization, he said 
this needs further consultation as it is the Hong Kong residents 
who pay for the construction of the airport. 

</TEXT>

