<F P=102>  OW2602055594 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2230 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2602055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News and Press Review" program] </F>
  [Text] Listeners. As a result of continued progress in 
broadcasting, recording, and media technology, effective 1 
March, the Central People's Radio Network will air casts under 
Program One, that have been originally broadcast via frequency 
106.1 MHz, in stereophonic instead of monophonic sound system. 
  While being broadcast in stereophonic sound system, casts -- 
especially literary casts -- in the Central People's Radio 
Network Program One will have characteristics such as treble and 
bass notes, a strong sense of reality, and a pleasant timbre to 
provide listeners with more melodious entertainment. 

