<H3> <TI>   Rural Women in Development Symposium Closes in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0103123994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1049 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0103123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 1 (XINHUA) -- A two-day symposium on 
rural women in development ended here today. 
  More than 100 specialists and scholars in sociology and 
women 
attended the symposium, which focused on the role of women in 
the socio-economic progress of underdeveloped areas and mutual 
aid among women in both economically developed and 
underdeveloped areas. 
  It also centered around topics such as education, 
technological extension and medical care for rural women in 
underdeveloped areas and effective means to finance the 
development of rural women in underdeveloped areas. 
  The symposium, the first of its kind held in China, was 
sponsored by the China features of the XINHUA NEWS AGENCY and 
the Rural Women's Development Research Center. 
  Chen Muhua, president of the All-China Women's Federation, 
and officials from some offices of U.N. organizations in China 
also attended today's meeting. 

</TEXT>

