<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yunnan People's Congress Committee Meeting Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2702024794 Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2702024794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The sixth meeting of the eighth provincial people's 
congress standing committee ended in Kunming this morning. 
Provincial people's congress Chairman Yin Jun presided over the 
session. The meeting ratified the draft namelist for members of 
the presidium, as well as the secretary general for the second 
session of the eighth provincial people's congress, and the 
draft agenda for this second session, to be submitted to the 
preparatory meeting for the second session of the eighth 
provincial people's congress for approval. In principle, the 
meeting ratified the draft work report of the Yunnan Provincial 
People's Congress Standing Committee; authorized Bao Yongkang, 
vice chairman of the provincial people's congress standing 
committee and its secretary general, to report to the second 
session of the eighth provincial people's congress; ratified the 
report on deputies' qualifications submitted by the Credentials 
Committee of the Eighth Yunnan Provincial People's Congress 
Standing Committee; decided on the namelist of participants who 
will attend the second session of the eighth provincial people's 
congress without the right to vote; ratified the decision of the 
Yunnan Provincial People's Congress Standing Committee on 
abolishing Xuanwei County and changing it to a city; and decided 
on the appointment of (Feng Xiankun) and Liu Ping as deputy 
secretaries general of the provincial people's congress standing 
committee. Vice chairmen of the provincial people's congress 
standing committee -- including Bao Yongkang, Yang Yitang, Yang 
Ming, Dao Guodong, Li Shuji, Bai Zuoguang, and Mai Ciqiu -- 
attended the meeting. Vice Governor Yang Jianqiang, and Wu 
Guangwen, deputy chief procurator of the provincial people's 
procuratorate, also were present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

