<H3> <TI>   Jilin Secretary Meets Hong Kong Members of CPPCC Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2302074094 Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2302074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The reception room of Nanhu Guesthouse was permeated 
with a lively and vigorous atmosphere on the afternoon of 22 
February. Provincial leaders He Zhukang, Gao Yan, Liu Yunzhao, 
Zhang Yueqi, Liu Xilin, Fang Jianyu, Zhang Tienan, and Hu Houjun 
came there to meet with the members from Hong Kong to attend the 
second session of the seventh provincial committee of the 
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC]. 
  He Zhukang, secretary of the provincial party committee, 
first extended a warm welcome to the members. He said: Jilin 
Province is a member of the big family of the motherland. Hong 
Kong compatriots are concerned about Jilin, and we are also 
concerned about Hong Kong. He urged the members to actively 
participate in and discuss the administration of state and 
government affairs, help in Jilin's opening to the outside 
world, and offer more ideas, suggestions, and views. 
  The provincial leaders and the members exchanged name cards 
and greeted each other. They held cordial discussions in a 
cheerful atmosphere. Governor Gao Yan and Vice Governor Liu 
Xilin introduced the reform in the finance, tax, and banking 
systems which the members were concerned about. 
  Liu Yunzhao, chairman of the provincial CPPCC committee, 
said 
that the suggestions and views offered by the members during the 
discussions at the session were delivered to provincial leaders 
in a written form. The members were pleased to hear this. They 
also offered the opinions and suggestions on the matters they 
respectively are concerned about. 
  In conclusion, the leaders and the members had a valuable 
group picture taken. 

</TEXT>

