<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaoning Convicts 18 `Hooligans,' Executes One </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2702031994 Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2702031994 </F>
<F P=104>  Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The major robbery case relating to a gang of 
hooligans, that had once caused a sensation throughout the 
province, was publicly tried by the Benxi city intermediate 
people's court on 26 February. The 18 criminal offenders 
relating to this case were respectively sentenced to death and 
set terms of imprisonment. 
  To the neglect of the state law, criminals, including (Zhang 
Hengju), hurt the people with tools, robbed the people of their 
property and materials, and raped women. They earned the bitter 
hatred of the people. 
  The Benxi city people's court sentenced (Zhang Hengju), the 
principal culprit, to death and deprived him of his lifelong 
political rights. (Hu Guangfa) and (Fan Pingjun), both repeat 
offenders, were sentenced to imprisonment for life and deprived 
of their lifelong political rights. (Li Yucheng), (Ying 
Yaoming), (Li Yan), and (Li Xue), also repeat offenders, were 
sentenced to imprisonment for 18 years or less. 
  After the trial, principal culprit (Zhang Hengju) was 
escorted to the execution ground and executed by shooting. 

</TEXT>

