<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhang Rongmao Elected New Shenyang Mayor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602142894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1400 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2602142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenyang, February 26 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Rongmao, a 
senior engineer, was elected mayor of Shenyang city, capital of 
Liaoning Province, at the second session of the city's eleventh 
people's congress, which closed today. 
  The former mayor, Wu Disheng, died in a helicopter crash in 
Israel last November. 
  Zhang, 56 years old, is from Taoyuan County in Hunan 
Province. He graduated from the graduate school of Dalian 
Institute of Industry in 1956 and he was among the first group 
of senior engineers in the environment protection field. 
  Before today's election, he served as vice-mayor of Shenyang 
city and deputy governor of Liaoning Province. Since January he 
has served as acting mayor of Shenyang city. 

</TEXT>

