<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Greets Opening of Civil Aviation Work Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2802144694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1326 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2802144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 28 (XINHUA) -- A national working 
conference on China's civil aviation opened here today. 
  Premier Li Peng sent a letter of greetings to the 
conference, 
calling on the staff members of the civil aviation services to 
enhance the sense of "safety first, punctual flights and best 
quality services". 
  He noted that China's civil aviation services are witnessing 
rapid growth. And he urged China's aviation services to deepen 
reform, carry out readjustment, and improve management so as to 
open up a new era in their work. 
  At the conference, Chen Guangyi, director of Civil Aviation 
Administration of China (CAAC), said that last year China's 
aviation services transported 33.71 million passengers and 
696,000 tons of goods and mails, respectively up by 16.8 and 21 
percent over the previous year. 
  Last year the air services in China also opened 63 new air 
routes and completed some airport extension projects. 
  Chen said that China's civil aviation services must practise 
scientific management with high standards and strict measures. 
  He also addressed the conference about the measures in the 
improvement of service quality in civil aviation services. 
  On the reform of civil aviation services, he said that the 
first step will focus on the quality of service. 
  He called for streamlining the relations between various 
airlines and subsidiaries and perfecting the contract system. 
  He said that the second step will focus on solutions to some 
deep-lying problems involving the whole administrative system 
and the functions of the various civil aviation administrations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

